      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ALTOCUMULUS (2) was strongly supported last start but missed the frame when fifth (23.42), beaten 7 lengths. Has a solid record from this box including two wins and a minor placing. Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. MCCRACKEN (4) showed good speed to score (30.72) off a middle draw two back then off a similar box last time settled off pace and could manage only a 4.5 lengths 4th at this track (26.05). Should be about the money. RIGHT TO RUN (1) jumped well and stalked the lead before boxing on to finish third (19.83) at Angle Park in Grade 6. Has been out the placings in all three runs here. Can measure up. HASTY HOLLY (6) was in the money last start in fast time - poses a threat again.",
